2.	In the absence of specific guideline regarding interest on capital paid by the firm to the partners, it was included in estimated as well as cost incurred and paid at the time of applying for registration and thereafter in quarterly compliance made under RERA upto 15/03/2019. However, after issue of Guidance note-1 dated 09-07-2019 I have reduced the interest cost on partner?s capital from the cost incurred and paid. 
3.	I am unable to certify the date of sale deed execution, PAN no and Mobile Number of the customer, since the necessary evidence is not in the possession of the firm.
4.	In respect of the all the booked flats on the date of issuing this certificate, the firm is not in possession of Agreement to sale details and in absence of information, I have mentioned the date of sale deed executed instead of date of agreement to sale. Further, I am unable to certify as to whether the firm had entered registered Agreement for Sale with buyers on receipt of consideration in excess of 10% of the apartment value.
5.	In respect of the below mentioned flats, the firm is not in possession of the registered agreement of sale, therefore date of agreement to sale is kept blank.
B1-101, B8-102, C3-504, A9-503,B6-103.
6.	Booking receipts from customers of Rs 44,36,000/- is deposited in bank account no 71761010017038 held with Syndicate bank, nanpura branch, surat which is not updated online in RERA Portal.
